vision.voltsofdoom.coresystem.universal.band_wagon

Annotation Type Stowaway


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={TYPE,METHOD})
public @interface Stowaway
    Indicates a type or method that the BandWagon should be made aware of (i.e. should recieve events). This annotation should only be applied to valid static methods, in order to subscribe only them, or to types, in order to subscribe all valid static methods in them.

    A method is considered "valid" if it:
    • is static
    • has only one argument
    • their one argument is a subclass of the event class.

    For a class:
    Indicates that all static methods with a single-argument constructor, where the type of their argument is an Event should be registered to the BandWagon.

    For a static method:
    Indicates that only this static method should be subscribed to the BandWagon
    Author:
    GenElectrovise
